03/02/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonia's ruling party, the Social Democratic Alliance for Macedonia, has invited a second ethnic Albanian party, the Party for Democratic Prosperity (PDP), to join the government coalition, <I>Utrinski Vesnik</I> daily reported Monday (3 February). Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski offered the PDP minister a seat in parliament and a deputy minister position. The government refused to comment on the report, and the other ethnic Albanian cabinet partner, the Democratic Union for Integration, said no one has discussed the possibility of PDP's entry into the cabinet.
In other news, main opposition VMRO-DPMNE elected former Finance Minister Nikola Gruevski as party deputy leader at the meeting of the party's central committee on Saturday (1 February). Four other former ministers - Ganka Samoilova-Cvetanovska, Ljupco Balkoski, Marjan Dodovski and Daniel Doncev - were elected members of the VMRO-DPMNE's executive committee. The leadership changes were carried out on initiative by VMRO-DPMNE leader Ljubco Georgievski. (Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 03/02/03; MIA, A1 TV - 01/02/03)
